  "title": "Spreading the greetings of Salam (Peace)",
  "source": "Hisn al-Muslim 224",
  "arabic": "قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم لاَ تَدْخُلُوا الْجَنَّةَ حَتَّى تُؤْمِنُوا وَلاَ تُؤْمِنُوا حَتَّى تَحَابُّوا أَوَلاَ أَدُلُّكُم عَلَى شَيْءٍ إِذَا فَعَلْتُمُوهُ تَحَابَبْتُم أَفْشُوا السَّلاَمَ بَيْنَكُمْ",
  "meaning": "The Messenger of Allah said: ‘You shall not enter paradise until you believe, and you shall not believe until you love one another. Shall I not inform you of something, if you were to act upon it, you will indeed achieve mutual love for one another? Spread the greeting amongst yourselves.",
